snippet.textDisplay:
I believe Swanand symbolizes the restless mind and its constant overthinking, while Shreya represents the heart, urging the mind to relax, stop overanalyzing, and live in the present. The mind (Swanand) creates endless, often unfounded scenarios, and the heart (Shreya) is gently advising it to just chill and let go.

Just beautiful.
